@gpeal We don't see what is the cause from the logs, but I would suspect the following code:

```java
//called from RecyclerViewAdapter.onBindViewHolder
public static void animate(final LottieAnimationView view) {
        Animator.AnimatorListener listener = new AnimatorListenerAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void onAnimationEnd(Animator animation) {
                view.removeAnimatorListener(this);
                view.setAnimation("loop.json", LottieAnimationView.CacheStrategy.Weak);
                view.loop(true);
                view.playAnimation();
            }
        };
        view.addAnimatorListener(listener);
        view.setTag(listener);

        view.setAnimation("intro.json", LottieAnimationView.CacheStrategy.Weak);
        view.loop(false);
        view.playAnimation();
    }
```

```java
//called from RecyclerViewAdapter.onViewRecycled
 public static void clear(LottieAnimationView view) {
        Animator.AnimatorListener listener = (Animator.AnimatorListener) view.getTag();
        if (listener != null) {
            view.removeAnimatorListener(listener);
        }
        view.clearAnimation();
    }
```
Can you see any problem with this logic?

@gpeal thanks, you are right, bind can be called many times, I have fixed that part, however it was not the cause for the issue.
I actually managed to reproduce the issue now and spotted the exact place it is happening. 

Animations has to be disabled in phone settings and than when we call animateFromTo we can observe this crash every time. 

```java
public static void animateFromTo(LottieAnimationView from, LottieAnimationView to) {
        to.cancelAnimation();
        to.setProgress(0);
        from.setVisibility(VISIBLE);
        to.setVisibility(VISIBLE);
        to.addAnimatorListener(new AnimatorListenerAdapter() {
            @Override
            public void onAnimationStart(Animator animation) {
                from.setVisibility(GONE);
                from.cancelAnimation();
                to.removeAnimatorListener(this);
            }
        });
        to.playAnimation();
    }
```

This method is obviously not the best one(it is not mine), but I still feel like it should not crash from inside Lottie...
In case we call "animateFromTo" in custom view constructor we get the original crash, however if we simply call it on button click we get more meaningful crash:

